Me

My name is Cole, and I’m a data scientist, statistician, writer, and aspiring data visualization professional. My preferred tools are R and ggplot2, including shiny and leaflet. I love a reason to make a fun map, enjoy data wrangling, and would love to explore more projects to grow my skillset.

Please check out these examples below, see some of the other stuff I’m up to on my website or Twitter. Drop me a line: coleman.reed.harris@gmail.com.

PD1

A collaborative project with researchers at Vanderbilt University, Stanford University, and Oregon Health and Sciences University. This visualization required some analysis to separate the data into clusters and visualize the differences in those clusters.

Nebula Genomics

A side project to collect and analyze Twitter data from Nebula Genomics.

Maps

A project to visualize differences in temparature and happiness levels across the United States using Leaflet and Shiny.
